# Better Auth

Auth is configured in `src/lib/server/auth.ts` and wired in `src/hooks.server.ts`.

## Server setup

```ts
import { betterAuth } from 'better-auth/minimal';
import { drizzleAdapter } from 'better-auth/adapters/drizzle';
import { sveltekitCookies } from 'better-auth/svelte-kit';
import { getRequestEvent } from '$app/server';

export const auth = betterAuth({
	baseURL: ORIGIN,
	secret: BETTER_AUTH_SECRET,
	database: drizzleAdapter(db, { provider: 'pg' }),
	plugins: [sveltekitCookies(getRequestEvent)] // must be last
});
```

## Hooks

```ts
import { svelteKitHandler } from 'better-auth/svelte-kit';

const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: event.request.headers });
if (session) {
	event.locals.user = session.user;
	event.locals.session = session.session;
}
return svelteKitHandler({ event, resolve, auth, building });
```

## Single admin (GitHub only)

- `emailAndPassword` disabled — GitHub OAuth only on `/login`
- `disableImplicitSignUp: true` on GitHub provider
- **No admin yet:** login shows **Sign up with GitHub** (`requestSignUp: true`) — first user becomes admin
- **Admin exists:** login shows **Sign in with GitHub** only — no signup for visitors
- `databaseHooks.user.create.before` rejects any second user
- Check `hasAdmin()` from `$lib/server/users` for UI and action guards

## Forms and actions

- Use `auth.api.signInSocial` with `requestSignUp` when bootstrapping admin
- Catch `APIError` from `better-auth/api` and return `fail(400, { message })`
- Protect routes in `load` via `event.locals.user` + `redirect(302, '/login')`
- Types: `User`, `Session` from `better-auth` in `app.d.ts` `Locals`
